content.content: In the introduction of UNI tokens, linked at https://uniswap.org/blog/uni/, it is stated that: ‘’’ In the meantime, UNI holders will have immediate ownership of:  Uniswap governance UNI community treasury The protocol fee switch eth ENS Uniswap Default List (tokens.uniswap.eth)  SOCKS liquidity tokens ‘’’  Can someone go into deeper detail about what UNI holders own specifically in regards to ‘eth ENS’ and ‘SOCKS liquidity tokens’ Thanks

Uniswap controls these LP tokens: https://etherscan.io/token/0x22d8432cc7aa4f8712a655fc4cdfb1baec29fca9?a=0x37c3791bea30744a88b9292f0c3b0cd3c4969d09 These have monetary value, as well as meme value    twitter.com    mikedemarais.eth (mikedemarais)  in case you missed it,  $UNI holders own/control/govern $133,000 of $SOCKS liquidity tokens https://t.co/EPzzTZwCBV Neeraj Thakur Δ @NeerajT4$UNI holders will have immediate ownership of:  - @UniswapProtocol governance. - UNI community treasury. - The protocol fee switch. - $eth ENS. - Uniswap Default List (tokens.uniswap.eth). - $SOCKS liquidity tokens.    10:41 PM - 16 Sep 2020     21            Uniswap also controls this ENS domain name: https://etherscan.io/enslookup-search?search=uniswap.eth This could be useful for pointing to decentralized content (eg. Uniswap user interfaces hosted on IPFS that are more difficult to take down vs traditional websites).
